    "b-component-themes-intro-2": {
      "id": "b-component-themes-intro-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "A component theme file is a sparse map at "
        },
        {
          "insert": "components/<surface>.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ". "
        },
        {
          "insert": "THEME_TOKEN_REGISTRY",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " is the closed runtime vocabulary that maps each accepted file and key to one or more CSS variables. The variables and their visual meanings are specified by "
        },
        {
          "insert": "Tokens",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "10-system-design/50-editor-design/40-visual-system/10-tokens"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-component-themes-registry-heading-7": {
      "id": "b-component-themes-registry-heading-7",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Registry and Validation"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-component-themes-registry-table-3": {
      "id": "b-component-themes-registry-table-3",
      "type": "structured-table",
      "props": {
        "columns": [
          "Stage",
          "Mechanic"
        ],
        "rows": [
          [
            "Registry",
            "Each file/key entry declares CSS vars and a color, length, or number kind. Length and number entries also carry min, max, step, and default metadata."
          ],
          [
            "Folder read",
            "readThemeDefinition drops unknown files and keys. A registered value survives only as a non-empty string or a { light, dark } string pair."
          ],
          [
            "Rail read",
            "normalizeComponentOverrides keeps registered pairs only. Colors must be six-digit hex; lengths and numbers must parse inside their registry range."
          ],
          [
            "Compilation",
            "compileThemeCss writes every mapped variable into light and dark blocks. A scalar value is copied to both modes."
          ],
          [
            "Runtime overlay",
            "styleRailVars maps sparse rail overrides through the same registry. A default-valued length or number becomes null and removes the inline property."
          ]
        ]
      },
      "children": []
    },
    "b-component-themes-example-4": {
      "id": "b-component-themes-example-4",
      "type": "code",
      "props": {
        "annotations": [
          {
            "lines": "1-4",
            "label": "themes/example/components/inline-code.json",
            "note": "Only the registered keys this theme overrides are present."
          }
        ],
        "language": "json"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "{\n  \"fg\": { \"light\": \"#0b6e99\", \"dark\": \"#529cca\" },\n  \"bg\": { \"light\": \"#e7f3f8\", \"dark\": \"#173d4d\" }\n}"
        }
      ],
